    "question": "If the probability of heads \\( p \\) is set to \\( 0.5 \\) and tails \\( q \\) is \\( 0.5 \\), what is the probability of being in state \\( S_2 \\) after 5 tosses, given the initial conditions \\( S_1(1) = q \\), \\( S_2(1) = p \\), and \\( S_3(1) = 0 \\)?",
    "solution": "With \\( p = 0.5 \\) and \\( q = 0.5 \\), we will calculate \\( S_2(5) \\) using the difference equations:\n\n1. \\( S_1(n) = q S_1(n-1) + q S_2(n-1) \\)\n2. \\( S_2(n) = p S_1(n-1) \\)\n\nStarting with the initial conditions:\n- \\( S_1(1) = q = 0.5 \\)\n- \\( S_2(1) = p = 0.5 \\)\n- \\( S_3(1) = 0 \\)\n\nWe will calculate \\( S_1(n) \\) and \\( S_2(n) \\) for \\( n = 2, 3, 4, 5 \\):\n\nCalculating \\( S_1(2) \\) and \\( S_2(2) \\):\n\n1. \\( S_1(2) = 0.5 \\cdot 0.5 + 0.5 \\cdot 0.5 = 0.25 + 0.25 = 0.5 \\)\n2. \\( S_2(2) = 0.5 \\cdot 0.5 = 0.25 \\)\n\nCalculating \\( S_1(3) \\) and \\( S_2(3) \\):\n\n1. \\( S_1(3) = 0.5 \\cdot 0.5 + 0.5 \\cdot 0.25 = 0.25 + 0.125 = 0.375 \\)\n2. \\( S_2(3) = 0.5 \\cdot 0.5 = 0.25 \\)\n\nCalculating \\( S_1(4) \\) and \\( S_2(4) \\):\n\n1. \\( S_1(4) = 0.5 \\cdot 0.375 + 0.5 \\cdot 0.25 = 0.1875 + 0.125 = 0.3125 \\)\n2. \\( S_2(4) = 0.5 \\cdot 0.375 = 0.1875 \\)\n\nCalculating \\( S_1(5) \\) and \\( S_2(5) \\):\n\n1. \\( S_1(5) = 0.5 \\cdot 0.3125 + 0.5 \\cdot 0.1875 = 0.15625 + 0.09375 = 0.25 \\)\n2. \\( S_2(5) = 0.5 \\cdot 0.3125 = 0.15625 \\)\n\nThus, the probability of being in state \\( S_2 \\) after 5 tosses is:\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{0.15625}\n\\]",
